task_list.task_description: Create a digital art piece of a futuristic cityscape.

input_params.name: prompt

The prompt is essential for guiding the model in creating visually striking digital art images based on the user's input, enabling users to convert their ideas into unique digital artworks.

task_list.task_description: Create a digital art piece based on the theme 'A futuristic cityscape at night'.
Convert the generated digital art piece into PDF format for a presentation.

input_params.name: prompt
input_params.description: The 'prompt' parameter is a user prompt in string data type, which serves as the input for this API. It describes the desired content or concept for the digital artwork generation process. The prompt is essential for guiding the model in creating visually striking digital art images based on the user's input, enabling users to convert their ideas into unique digital artworks.

input_params.name: file
input_params.description: The 'file' parameter should be a binary image file in one of the supported formats: JPEG, PNG, GIF, BMP, TIFF, PBM, PGM, or PPM. This parameter is required for the 'image_to_pdf_conversion' API to receive the input image file that will be converted to a PDF document. The API processes the provided image file and generates a PDF output, enabling users to efficiently transform visual content into a universally accessible format for sharing, printing, or archiving purposes.

task_list.task_description: Generate a graffiti art image with the theme 'Urban jungle'.
Resize the generated graffiti art image to 800x600 pixels for a website banner.

input_params.name: prompt
input_params.description: The 'prompt' parameter is a user-provided textual prompt in string data type. It serves as the input for the 'tti_Graffiti_Art' API, allowing users to input their creative ideas or prompts to generate graffiti-style images. This parameter is essential for the API to transform the user's textual input into visually appealing graffiti art.

input_params.name: width
input_params.description: The 'width' parameter specifies the desired width dimension for resizing the user-uploaded image file. This parameter is essential for determining the new width of the image during the resizing process. It plays a crucial role in adjusting the dimensions of the image according to user requirements, ensuring the output meets the specified width criteria for the resized image.

input_params.name: height
input_params.description: The height parameter specifies the desired height dimension for resizing the user-uploaded image file. This parameter is essential for determining the final dimensions of the resized image, ensuring that the output meets the user's requirements for image size adjustments.

input_params.name: file
input_params.description: The 'file' parameter of datatype 'binary_image_file' is required for this API as it serves as the input containing the image file uploaded by the user. This parameter is essential for the 'Image_Resizing' API to receive the binary form of the image file, enabling the resizing process to be carried out on the user-provided visual content.
